Job Description
Develop and design advanced software applications for driverless technology company. Duties include: Build a highly reliable, scalable, and cost effective platform to search for impactful on-road scenarios, label data, prepare resulting dataset for model training, and close the model performance feedback loop. Explore, prototype, validate, and iterate new algorithms and models. Drive efforts to optimize, supervise and refine on-road performance for models on the
path to production. Serve as a technical leader within the department and guide current and future technology choices. Understand the business and operational impact for different technology tradeoffs and balance them effectively based on the company’s need. Enable others engineers on the team to be more effective through design and code that is easy to extend and contribute into. May telecommute.
&#xa;&#xa;
Additional Job Description
REQUIREMENTS: Master’s degree or foreign equivalent degree in Computer Science, Electrical Engineering, Computer Engineering, Data Science, Mathematics, or a related field and Three years of work experience as a Senior Software Engineer, Machine Learning Engineer, Research Engineer, Member of Technical Staff, or a related occupation. Background, education, or experience must include:
1. Building highly scalable platforms using Python, C, or C++;
2. Knowledge of operating systems, including Linux;
3. Experience with data platforms, including Hadoop and Spark;
4. Experience with building autonomous driving software and technologies, including ROS and PyTorch;
5. Data mining techniques and tools, including SQL, NoSQL, sklearn, Pattern recognition, and anomaly detection;
6. Experience with developing and deploying machine learning systems;
7. Experience with cloud computing platforms, including AWS, Google Cloud, and Azure;
8. Software architecture and system design;
9. Knowledge of algorithms and data structures;
10. Containerization and orchestration tools, including Docker and Kubernetes;
11. Experience in continuous integration and continuous deployment (CI/CD) pipelines.
